modules.description: Provides functions to define Vue.js components with type-safe data bindings, including methods, computed properties, and event handlers. Works with OCaml records, variants, and polymorphic variants to structure component data and props. Enables direct integration of OCaml types into Vue templates for reactive application development.

This module provides operations for manipulating OCaml AST elements, including constructing, transforming, and traversing expressions, core types, and value bindings, with support for ppxlib and Astlib structures. It enables tasks like code generation, type conversion, and syntax analysis, particularly in ppx rewriter contexts, by handling location tracking, accumulators, and specific language features such as directives and attributes.
